description: Recently sold: $255,000. This historic home was built for city founder Edward Phalen, and passed off to Edmund Rice... maybe you've heard of them; their namesakes (Lake Phalen and Rice Street) are just blocks away. This home retains natural woodwork, solid doors, hardwood floors, and very high ceilings. It has a huge yard, an unbeatable view of the city, and is reputed to be one of the highest points in St.Paul. It has an oversized, heated 3-car garage with pull-down stairs for storage. New driveway and patio (2018), siding (2016); real fireplaces (one with original, ornate stonework), 3 pellet stoves (main level, attic, garage). This property has been licensed for rental and is set up to be two independent units. The main entryway can be used to access the top and bottom units separately, and independently. Main level, there are 2 bed, a 3/4 bath, a 4-season porch, and a kitchen, living and dining room. Second level, 2 bed, full bath, kitchen/living, and full attic bedroom.

Enjoy the convenience and affordability of this well maintained 2bd/1ba lower level duplex. With tons of natural light this charming space has tons of room to make your own. The home offers TWO HUUUGE BEDROOMS, with large closets, an updated kitchen with stainless steel appliances and gas stove. The eat-in kitchen boasts plenty of cabinet space, With room for an island. The bathroom is also very spacious with deep tub great for relaxing.

This home is conveniently located just minutes from downtown, and close to 35E, and Phalen Blvd. Enjoy several neighborhood parks within walking distance, such as Wilder Park and Cayuga Park. Lake Phalen is also just minutes from your door. This home has a large yard- perfect for entertaining.

Tenant is ONLY responsible for electricity, gas and for snow removal. Owner pays water/sewer and trash as well as lawn care.

This is a professionally managed building from the folks at Housing Hub. Secure Online Tenant Portals makes paying rent and scheduling maintenance a breeze. Housing Hub wants to provide you with a great living experience!

This building is pet friendly, however, some breed restrictions and pet fees will apply.

Please make sure to mention this address when leaving a message or sending a text.

Here is our application selection criteria for your review:

1. Preferred credit score of 650 or above
2. Good rental history - No evictions, UDs or judgments
3. Clean criminal history - No felonies
4. Income should be 2.5 times the rent

All information deemed reliable but not guaranteed.
